<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,538,793,819]" box="[189,538,793,819]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,538,793,819]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,538,793,819]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Morphological observations</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,843,1335]" box="[234,607,843,869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,607,843,869]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Light microscopy (
<figureCitation box="[468,599,843,869]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 29-49</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,843,1335]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Frustules in girdle view rectangular, bent around the transapical axis (
<figureCitation box="[974,1104,882,908]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 29, 30</figureCitation>
).Valves linear-lanceolate with parallel to slightly convex margins and clearly protracted, rostrate, occasionally subcapitate apices (
<figureCitation box="[197,330,959,986]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 31-49</figureCitation>
). Valve dimensions (n=25): length 
<quantity box="[740,863,959,986]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15 µm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[950,1088,960,986]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.7 µm</quantity>
. Raphe valve (
<figureCitation box="[1261,1390,959,986]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 31-40</figureCitation>
) concave with a linear axial area, narrow to almost absent near the valve apices, hardly widening towards the central part of the valve. Central area irregular, formed by several more widely spaced striae. Raphe straight, filiform, invisible, with indistinct straight, simple proximal raphe endings. Distal raphe hardly discernible in LM. Striae slightly radiate throughout the entire valve, becoming more radiate and more densely spaced near the apices, 
<quantity box="[559,668,1153,1180]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.001" metricValueMax="8.382" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="in" value="31.5" valueMax="33.0" valueMin="30.0">30– 33 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[675,753,1154,1180]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
, up to 
<quantity box="[830,933,1153,1180]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0413999999999999" metricValueMax="1.0668" metricValueMin="1.016" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="in" value="41.0" valueMax="42.0" valueMin="40.0">40–42 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[940,1016,1154,1180]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
near the valve apices. Rapheless valve (
<figureCitation box="[272,406,1192,1218]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 41-49</figureCitation>
) slightly convex with very narrow, linear axial area, widening to form a weakly elliptically, never transapically elongated central area, never forming a fascia or subfascia. Central striae slightly more distantly spaced. Striae slightly radiate throughout, only slightly more denser near the apices, 
<quantity box="[277,381,1308,1335]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.874" metricValueMax="8.128" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="in" value="31.0" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="30.0">30–32 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[388,467,1309,1335]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1377,1831]" box="[234,762,1377,1404]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,762,1377,1404]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Scanning electron microscopy (
<figureCitation box="[623,755,1377,1403]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 50-53</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1377,1831]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Striae in the raphe valve composed of a series of 3 
<emphasis box="[784,799,1417,1442]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">–</emphasis>
4 distinct, rounded to square areolae terminating in one transapically elongated, rectangular areola (
<figureCitation box="[754,842,1455,1482]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Central striae composed of 2 rounded areolae and one transapically elongated areola near the valve margin (
<figureCitation box="[952,1044,1494,1521]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Occasionally, short slit-like areolae interposed between the central striae. Near the apices, striae only composed of 2–3 rounded areolae (
<figureCitation box="[293,383,1571,1598]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Mantle areolae elongated, slit-like. Striae on the rapheless valve composed of 2–5 irregularly shaped (mostly rounded or elongated rectangular) areolae (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1113,1610,1637]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Near the apices, striae showing lowest number of areolae (
<figureCitation box="[634,727,1649,1676]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Internal areolae openings on both valves covered by hymenes (
<figureCitation box="[310,448,1687,1714]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 52, 53</figureCitation>
). External raphe branches straight to weakly curved terminating in simple, short proximal and distal raphe endings (
<figureCitation box="[600,687,1726,1753]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Distal raphe endings terminating just beyond the last apical stria (
<figureCitation box="[256,344,1765,1792]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Internally, proximal raphe endings short, slightly bent. Distal raphe endings terminating in small helictoglossae (
<figureCitation box="[472,560,1804,1831]" captionStart="Figs 29-53" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,740,1783]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 29-53. Achnanthidium maritimo-antarcticum Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalová sp. nov. Light and scanning electron micrographs of the type population on Byers Peninsula (Livingston Island). 29-30. LM views of some frustules in girdle view. 31-40. LM views of raphe valves. 41-49. LM views of rapheless valves. 50. SEM external view of an entire raphe valve. 51. SEM external view of an entire rapheless valve. 52. SEM internal view of an entire raphe valve. 53. SEM internal view of an entire rapheless valve. Scale bars represent 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3835056/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
