<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,800,267,293]" box="[189,800,267,293]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,800,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,800,267,293]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ecology, distribution and associated diatom flora</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,314,664]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The type population of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van de Vijver &amp; Kopalova" authorityYear="2014" box="[462,752,315,341]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Achnanthidiaceae" genus="Achnanthidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Achnanthales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="maritimo-antarcticum">
<emphasis box="[462,752,315,341]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. maritimo-antarcticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in a large lake located on the central plateau of Byers Peninsula. The lake is characterized by a weakly alkaline pH (7.5) and a low conductivity (130 µS/cm). The ion composition in the lake is mainly dominated by Na 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1118,1128,384,398]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">+</superScript>
(20.0 mg/l) and Ca 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1380,1399,384,398]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">2+</superScript>
(
<quantity box="[198,290,422,449]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.21" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mg" value="12.1">12.1mg</quantity>
/l). Both nutrients (N-NO 
<subScript attach="left" box="[587,596,440,454]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">3</subScript>
+N-NO 
<subScript attach="left" box="[685,694,440,454]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">2</subScript>
) and phosphate were rather low (
<quantity box="[1089,1157,421,448]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mg" value="25.0">25 µg</quantity>
/l and 
<quantity box="[1233,1300,422,448]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mg" value="10.0">10 µg</quantity>
/l resp.). The shoreline of the lake was completely covered with partly submerged mosses. Dominant taxa in the sample included 
<taxonomicName box="[384,622,493,519]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Fragilariaceae" genus="Fragilaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fragilariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="capucina">
<emphasis box="[384,622,493,519]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fragilaria capucina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[627,661,493,519]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Desm. (
<bibRefCitation author="Desmazieres J. B. H. J." box="[755,975,493,520]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref8000" refString="Desmazieres J. B. H. J. 1825. Plantes cryptogames du Nord de la France. Leleux, Lille." type="book" year="1825">Desmazières 1825</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[994,1145,493,519]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Fragilariaceae" genus="Staurosirella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fragilariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[994,1145,493,519]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Staurosirella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<taxonomicName authority="Van de Vijver &amp; Zidarova in Van" authorityName="Van de Vijver &amp; Zidarova in Van" authorityYear="2011" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Navicula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Naviculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="cremeri">
<emphasis box="[1197,1398,493,519]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Navicula cremeri</emphasis>
Van de Vijver &amp; Zidarova 
<emphasis box="[493,516,530,555]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">in</emphasis>
Van
</taxonomicName>
de Vijver 
<emphasis box="[684,742,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Vijver B. &amp; Zidarova R. &amp; Sterken M. &amp; Verleyen E. &amp; de Haan M. &amp; Vyverman W. &amp; Hinz F. &amp; Sabbe K." box="[755,1058,529,556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="281 - 297" refId="ref10656" refString="Van de Vijver B., Zidarova R., Sterken M., Verleyen E., de Haan M., Vyverman W., Hinz F. &amp; Sabbe K. 2011 d. Revision of the genus Navicula s. s. (Bacillariophyceae) in inland water of the Sub-Antarctic and Antarctic with the description of 5 new species. Phycologia 50: 281 - 297. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2216 / 10 - 49.1" type="journal article" year="2011">
Van de Vijver 
<emphasis box="[921,978,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
2011d
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[1120,1229,529,555]" class="Monogenea" family="Capsalidae" genus="Nitzschia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Capsalidea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1120,1229,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nitzschia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[1271,1392,530,555]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">perminuta</emphasis>
. Smaller populations were found in other lakes such as Limnopolar Lake but these populations never exceed 1% of the total diatom composition. Due to force-fitting and taxonomic drift, the distribution of the new taxon in the Antarctic Region is unclear.
</paragraph>
